d that catching UnsupportedFeature Error silently can cause problems—should we improve robustness by using `java.class.path`?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining code handling for CodeSource**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to improve the code that handles `CodeSource`. I need to ensure that we import File, Arrays, and LinkedHashSet, and then check that the set is non-empty. However, there might be issues with Native Image support where `Class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource()` could return null. This could lead to problems if no classpath scanning happens in a native context. Should I consider creating a custom classpath root from actual class bytes? This could help with loading generated bytecode dynamically, even though that's not typically supported.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering TestClassScanner functionality**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how the TestClassScanner works to discover class names from class files. It attempts to load these classes using the default class loader. If the class is already present in the image and the name matches, it can successfully load the class. This is an interesting mechanism that might help streamline the loading process, but I need to ensure it integrates well within the existing workflow. Would there be edge cases I need to watch out for?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented coverage-focused test for `org.springframework.test.context.aot.TestClassScanner`.\n\nChanged files:\n- `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build.gradle`\n  - Added JUnit Jupiter 6.0.0 and JUnit Platform launcher runtime dependency so Spring’s scanner can discover JUnit class-template tests.\n\n- `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/TestClassScannerTest.java`\n  - Added a dedicated public test class for `TestClassScanner`.\n  - Exercises the public/protected AOT scanning path via a `TestAotProcessor` subclass.\n  - Uses a Spring-enabled JUnit `@ParameterizedClass` with `@Nested` classes to drive `TestClassScanner.collectNestedTestClasses(...)`, reaching the remaining `Class#getDeclaredClasses()` call site.\n  - Handles Native Image unsupported dynamic classpath scanning via `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)` as required.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00379dc1523df55f016a298310670c8197b5f61cc770b89764\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 419, "output": 1148, "cacheRead": 53760, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55327, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781105401007, "responseId": "resp_00379dc1523df55f016a2982f99474819783d112f7323d98a6"}}
